Are you okay with inserting after the found node instead of before it? That can be done with a small change in your method.
```
    public void insertAtAnyPoint(int data, int pos) {
        Node last = findNode(pos);
        if (Node.count == 0) this.insert(data);
        else {
            Node temp = last;
            last = new Node(data);
            last.next = temp.next;
            temp.next=last;
        }
    }
``` 
Inserting before the found node will need the findNode to return previous node to where you want to insert it being a singly linked list.

Inserting before position:
```
    public Node findNodeToInsert(int d) {
        Node found = head;
        Node prev = null;
        while (found.next != null) {
            if (found.data == d)
            {
                break;
            }
            prev = found;
            found = found.next;
        }
        return prev;
    }
    
    public void insertAtAnyPoint(int data, int pos) {
        if (Node.count == 0) this.insert(data);
        else {
            Node last = findNodeToInsert(pos);
            Node temp = last;
            last = new Node(data);
            last.next = temp.next;
            temp.next=last;
        }
    }
```

